# ==============================================================================
# SpellStars Environment Configuration
# ==============================================================================
#
# REQUIRED: Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
#
# Quick Start:
#   1. Copy: cp .env.example .env (or manually copy on Windows)
#   2. Get credentials from: https://supabase.com/dashboard
#      - Select your project
#      - Go to Settings > API
#      - Copy "Project URL" and "anon public" key
#   3. Replace values below with your credentials
#   4. Restart dev server: npm run dev
#
# ==============================================================================

# Supabase Project URL
# Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project URL
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url_here

# Supabase Anonymous Key (Public)
# Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API keys > anon public
# This key is safe to use in client-side code (it's protected by RLS policies)
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# ==============================================================================
# Alternative: Using Doppler for Secret Management (Recommended for Teams)
# ==============================================================================
#
# Doppler provides secure secret management and eliminates the need for .env files
#
# Setup Instructions:
#   1. Install Doppler CLI:
#      Windows: scoop install doppler
#      Mac: brew install doppler
#      Linux: See https://docs.doppler.com/docs/install-cli
#
#   2. Login to Doppler:
#      doppler login
#
#   3. Setup project:
#      doppler setup
#
#   4. Run app with Doppler:
#      doppler run -- npm run dev
#
# Benefits:
#   - No .env file needed
#   - Secrets synced across team
#   - Automatic secret rotation
#   - Audit logs for secret access
#
# See: https://docs.doppler.com for complete documentation
#
# ==============================================================================

# ==============================================================================
# Migration Scripts Only (Not needed for app runtime)
# ==============================================================================
#
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN is ONLY required for PowerShell migration scripts:
#   - push-migration.ps1
#   - check-migrations.ps1
#   - check-schema.ps1
#   - check-tables.ps1
#
# This token is NOT used by the application itself.
#
# To get your access token:
#   1. Go to: https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
#   2. Click "Generate new token"
#   3. Give it a name (e.g., "SpellStars Migrations")
#   4. Copy the token and paste below
#   5. Store securely - it has full admin access to your projects
#
# If using Doppler, store this token in Doppler instead
#
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here

# ==============================================================================
# Troubleshooting
# ==============================================================================
#
# Error: "Missing Supabase environment variables"
#   - Ensure .env file exists in project root
#   - Verify both VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are set
#   - Check for typos in variable names (must start with VITE_)
#   - Restart dev server after creating/modifying .env
#
# Error: "Invalid API key"
#   - Verify you copied the "anon public" key, not "service_role"
#   - Check for extra spaces or line breaks in the key
#   - Ensure key is from the correct Supabase project
#
# Error: "Failed to fetch"
#   - Verify VITE_SUPABASE_URL is correct and includes https://
#   - Check your Supabase project is active (not paused)
#   - Verify your internet connection
#
# For more help, see:
#   - docs/DEPLOYMENT.md
#   - docs/QUICKSTART.md
#   - https://supabase.com/docs
#
# ==============================================================================
